  "text": "Constraints on the blood volume fractions in the scalp and brain were guided by values from the literature. Normal blood volume fractions are approximately 4% in the skin [CITATION_1] and 5.2 ± 1.4% in the gray matter of the brain [CITATION_2] . The arterial volume fraction in the brain is approximately 30% [CITATION_3] , meaning that capillary plus venous blood volume fraction is in the range of 70%. With these values as a general guideline and recognizing that the actual blood volume and composition may vary significantly depending on exactly where the NIRS detectors are placed relative to vascular structures, we choose the following bounds happens for the scalp blood volume fraction 0:01 < F s;bv < 0:06;",
